    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Local Open Scope category_scope.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** ** Definition of [A\u1d52\u1d56] *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition opposite\n           C D\n           (F : Functor C D)\n           (G : Functor D C)\n           (A : F -| G)\n: G^op -| F^op\n  := @Build_AdjunctionUnitCounit\n       _ _ (G^op) (F^op)\n       ((counit A)^op)\n       ((unit A)^op)\n       (unit_counit_equation_2 A)\n       (unit_counit_equation_1 A).",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Local Notation \"A ^op\" := (opposite A) : adjunction_scope.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Local Open Scope adjunction_scope.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** ** [\u1d52\u1d56] is judgmentally involutive *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition opposite_involutive C D (F : Functor C D) (G : Functor D C) (A : F -| G)\n: (A^op)^op = A\n  := idpath.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Module Export AdjointDualNotations.",
      "messages": [],
